Biography

Patrick Benjamin Guinness was born on 10 March 1931.

He was the son of G/Capt. Thomas Loel Evelyn Bulkeley Guinness and Hon. Joan Barbara Yarde-Buller

He married Dolores Maria Agatha Wilhelmine Luise Gräfin von Fürstenberg, daughter of Franz Egon Graf von Fürstenberg and Gloria Rubio, on 22 October 1955.

He died on 5 October 1965 at age 34, killed in a motoring accident.

Patrick Benjamin Guinness also went by the nick-name of Tara.

He was educated at Eton College, Windsor, Berkshire, England. He gained the rank of Lieutenant in the service of the Royal Horse Guards (Blues).

Children of Patrick Benjamin Guinness and Dolores Maria Agatha Wilhelmine Luise Gräfin von Fürstenberg
